<task id="016" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-06 Add additive PaneEventBus event types (5 new) per ADR-030</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>1 hour</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G3 (parallel-safe within group; foundational for 017, 018, 020, 021)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, event-bus, pane-event, adr-030</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the closed 4-channel `PaneEventBus` typed-union with 5 additive event-type
    discriminants required by the R5 chat-driven Summarize vertical slice. Per ADR-030
    the bus channel set is permanently closed at 4 (`workspace` | `context` |
    `conversation` | `safety`); event-type discriminants WITHIN those channels are
    additive. This task adds the five discriminants needed by downstream R5 widgets
    (`StructuredOutputStreamWidget`, `FilePreviewContextWidget`, chat-pane UX, per-file
    affordance) so they can publish/subscribe to the events the vertical slice requires.

    New discriminants (verbatim per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4 and spec.md NFR-09):
    - `workspace.streaming_started`
    - `workspace.field_delta`
    - `workspace.streaming_complete`
    - `context.files_staged`
    - `context.file_selected`

    The task is **strictly additive**: existing subscribers MUST keep working unchanged
    because TypeScript discriminated-union narrowing on `event.type === '<existing>'`
    skips the new branches as "unknown" discriminants. No edits to existing event-type
    structures, no new channels, no new feature flags, and NO BFF code change (frontend
    types only → BFF publish-size delta = 0).

    The work is small (2h) but high-leverage: tasks 017, 018, 020, 021 all subscribe to
    or dispatch on these types. Getting the field set right, the channel placement
    right, and the exhaustive-switch audit right prevents downstream rework.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript developer familiar with discriminated-union design, ADR-030
    PaneEventBus contract, and the closed-4-channel architecture of the R5 SpaarkeAi
    shell. Comfortable auditing every consumer of a shared union for exhaustive-switch
    impact + backward compatibility.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts` defines 5 new
    additive event-type discriminants placed within the existing 4 channels per the
    list above (3 on `workspace`, 2 on `context`). `WorkspacePaneEvent.type` and
    `ContextPaneEvent.type` unions are extended with the new literals; matching
    payload-shape fields (e.g. `fieldPath`, `fieldContent`, `sequence`, `fileIds`,
    `selectedFileId`) are added as optional fields with JSDoc tying them to the
    new discriminants. No 5th channel is added. No existing event-type literal is
    edited. `@spaarke/ai-widgets` builds clean; all downstream consumers
    (`@spaarke/ui-components`, `@spaarke/legal-workspace`, `@spaarke/events-components`,
    `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`, `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`) build clean. The
    exhaustive-switch audit is recorded in task notes (zero `never` exhaustiveness
    sites identified, OR any identified sites have new cases added or explicit
    no-op documented). ADR-030 compliance verified. Quality gates pass.
  </goal>

