    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Additive event-type literal" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts">
        Existing `WorkspacePaneEvent.type` is a string-literal union of 11 discriminants
        (`'widget_load' | 'widget_update' | ... | 'active_widget_changed'`). Add the 3
        new workspace literals (`'streaming_started'`, `'field_delta'`,
        `'streaming_complete'`) to the union. Existing `ContextPaneEvent.type` is a
        union of 3 (`'context_update' | 'context_highlight' | 'stage_change'`). Add the
        2 new context literals (`'files_staged'`, `'file_selected'`).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Optional discriminant-scoped fields" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts">
        Look at how `wizardId` / `wizardAction` / `fieldName` / `fieldValue` are added
        as optional fields tied to `type === 'wizard_step'`, documented under a `// ──
        wizard_step fields ──` comment block. Follow this exact convention for new
        fields tied to `streaming_*` and `files_*` / `file_*` discriminants.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="JSDoc on the union literal" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts">
        The doc-comment on the `type` union itself lists each discriminant on its own
        line with a `—` describing intent. Add the same one-line description for each
        new discriminant inline with the existing list.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice. The user uploads
      files in the chat (Conversation pane), the orchestrator streams `FieldDelta`
      SSE events from the BFF (task 005 / D1-05), and a new `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
      (task 017 / D2-07) renders the structured output progressively in the Workspace
      pane. The widget needs to be told (a) when streaming begins
      (`workspace.streaming_started`), (b) each field delta as it arrives
      (`workspace.field_delta`), and (c) when streaming is complete
      (`workspace.streaming_complete`). Separately, when the user stages files
      (`context.files_staged`) or selects one for preview (`context.file_selected`),
      the new `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018 / D2-09) reacts in the Context pane.

      All 5 events are first-class members of the existing 4-channel PaneEventBus
      typed union per ADR-030's "channels closed; types additive" discipline. Adding
      them is a pre-requisite for tasks 017, 018, 020, and 021.
    </background>
    <dependencies>none — additive type union; no upstream task required</dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 017 (D2-07) `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` SUBSCRIBES to
        `workspace.streaming_started`, `workspace.field_delta`,
        `workspace.streaming_complete`. Blocked on task 016.</item>
      <item>Task 018 (D2-09) `FilePreviewContextWidget` SUBSCRIBES to
        `context.files_staged`, `context.file_selected`. Blocked on task 016.</item>
      <item>Task 020 (D2-11) Chat-pane orchestration UX DISPATCHES
        `context.files_staged` on file upload, `workspace.streaming_started/complete`
        when summarize runs. Blocked on task 016.</item>
      <item>Task 021 (D2-12) "Summarize this only" per-file affordance DISPATCHES
        `context.file_selected`. Blocked on task 016.</item>
      <item>R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4 lists the 5 event types verbatim. Spec NFR-09 cites the
        same list. R5 design phase confirmed channel set stays at 4.</item>
      <item>The path-drift note in task 001 (sub-agent finding) — plan.md / spec.md /
        CLAUDE.md reference `infra/ai-search/` but the actual repo path is
        `infrastructure/ai-search/`. This task uses ACTUAL repo paths.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

